    "passives": {
      "CloneResolvePassiveAGokuBrideBoss": {
        "id": "CloneResolvePassiveAGokuBrideBoss",
        "found": true,
        "localization": {
          "name": "Clone Expertise",
          "description": "If this unit is not conjured, this unit enters battle with 3 Charges, and Counter Stance for 150TU. If this unit is conjured, this unit enters battle with 1 Charge and the Armor status effect.\n\nIf this unit is charged, not burning, and there are 2+ non-conjured allies on the battlefield, each time this unit takes damage from an attack and survives until after the end of the turn with less than 50% of max HP, this unit will will spend a Charge to add another Sun Wukong to the next in line of allied reinforcements.\n\nAdd another Sun Wukong to the next in line of allied reinforcements when this unit is defeated by an enemy attack. This effect triggers if this unit is not conjured and has a Charge. This is not considered a revenge passive skill.\n\nEach time this unit damages an enemy with an attack while charged, this unit will spend a charge to get another turn. This effect can trigger again against the same unit. Effects that influence TU order may interrupt the extra turn (e.g. Stuns targeting the lowest TU target).\n\nAll Sun Wukongs created by this unit will have matching Levels, Limit Breaks, Awakenings, Boosts, Potential, Mastery, Weapons, and Accessories. Counter Stance will overwrite status effects on this unit. The next time the unit with counter stance takes damage from an enemy attack, it will become their turn. Armor grants 50% damage reduction from the next attack, then the effect is removed."
        }
      },
      "CursedSleepEntryAGokuBrideBoss": {
        "id": "CursedSleepEntryAGokuBrideBoss",
        "found": true,
        "localization": {
          "name": "Heaven's Robe",
          "description": "If this unit would be defeated by an enemy attack or a status effect while having more than 1 HP, it instead survives with 1 HP.\n\nGrants all non-burning allies Stun Wards and Poison Wards. 1 random non-burning enemy is granted the Cursed Sleep status effect for 200TU. These effects are triggered when this unit enters the battlefield as a conjured unit. Each Ward prevents their named effect from being applied once, then is removed. Identical Wards cannot stack.\n\nWhenever this unit defeats a non-conjured enemy with an attack:\n\n- if charged, this unit spends a charge to add another Sun Wukong to the next in line of allied reinforcements.\n- this unit will grant the Cursed Sleep status effect for 200TU to the next enemy that enters the battlefield."
        }
      },
